{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04026/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04026"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:40:26"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["plan américain"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, crane, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman poses in a pink ballgown with her backside in front of the camera."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04026/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04026","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04026/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04026"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04026/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04026/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04026/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04026/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04026/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04026/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04026/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04026/canvas/1/33e945b1-4dc2-4779-9bb0-61fa0783ec03","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:10:14.214Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Although Spanish designer Cristóbal Balenciaga had a complicated relationship with the press, his work still needed to be photographed at times. By the mid-1950s, “a new crop of photographers had come along who did more for Balenciaga than words ever could. The <em>Bazaar</em>’s Richard Avedon photographed models in Balenciagas but his style was a bit too antic, while <em>Vogue</em> found a perfect match in the sensitive stillness of Irving Penn...If it was only Penn who was able to capture the sculptural quality of Balenciaga’s clothes, it took [his wife and model Lisa] Fonssagrives to dissipate their solemnity: no model has ever been so lovely and amused” (Blume, <em>The Master of Us All</em>, 126). This sculptural quality also describes Reynolds’s work in the film.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04026/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:683.4993270524899,293.86271870794087,189.9327052489906,587.8869448183041"}}}]}]}]}